s it that they had no rightful place, and yet they were exploited by foolish men and women?”</ref>

== Improper Worship in History ==
Improper worship—that which stands in opposition to the deities recognized by the state as orthodox—has consistently been ridiculed by scholars and, at times, forcibly suppressed. For example, during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Ping|de|Kaiser Ping|ja|平帝|zh|平帝|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Western Han|de|Westliche Han-Dynastie|ja|西漢|zh|西漢|12=draft}}, there was the decree “Ban the dissemination of teachings, prohibit improper worship, and permit the sounds of Zheng.” During the {{ill|Eastern Han|de|Östliche Han-Dynastie|ja|東漢|zh|東漢|12=draft}}, {{ill|Diwulun|de|Diwulun|ja|第五倫|zh|第五倫|12=draft}} decreed “Ban and eradicate improper worship, and the people will be at peace.” At the end of the Eastern Han, {{ill|Cao Cao|de|Cao Cao|ja|曹操|zh|曹操|12=draft}} ordered “Ban and sever improper worship; illicit relations and the flight of offenders led to a solemnity along county boundaries.” Later, {{ill|Emperor Wen of Wei|de|Kaiser Wen von Wei|ja|魏文帝|zh|魏文帝|12=draft}} issued an edict stating, “From now on, whoever dares to establish a rite not conforming to propriety, or whose shamanic words are uttered, shall be dealt with as following the heterodox path, as inscribed in the law.” Similarly, {{ill|Emperor Ming of Wei|de|Kaiser Ming von Wei|ja|魏明帝|zh|魏明帝|12=draft}} decreed, “For those mountains and rivers in the counties not included in the sacrificial canon, do not venerate them.” During the reign of {{ill|Emperor Wu of Jin|de|Kaiser Wu von Jin|ja|晉武帝|zh|晉武帝|12=draft}}, an edict stated “If it is not in the sacrificial canon, remove it.” Emperor Ming of the {{ill|Northern Wei|de|Northern Wei|ja|北魏|zh|北魏|12=draft}} decreed “Ban improper worship, and burn all miscellaneous deities.” In the {{ill|Northern Zhou|de|Nördliche Zhou|ja|北周|zh|北周|12=draft}}, {{ill|Emperor Wu|de|Kaiser Wu|ja|武帝|zh|武帝|12=draft}} ordered “Ban all improper worship; expel anything not recorded in the liturgical canon.” In the period of the {{ill|Southern and Northern Dynasties|de|Süd- und Nord-Dynastien|ja|南北朝|lt=Southe