of the {{ill|Northern Wei|de|Northern Wei|ja|北魏|zh|北魏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Northern Wei|qq=}} decreed “Ban improper worship, and burn all miscellaneous deities.” In the {{ill|Northern Zhou|de|Nördliche Zhou|ja|北周|zh|北周|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Northern Zhou|qq=}}, {{ill|Emperor Wu|de|Kaiser Wu|ja|武帝|zh|武帝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Wu|qq=}} ordered “Ban all improper worship; expel anything not recorded in the liturgical canon.” In the period of the {{ill|Southern and Northern Dynasties|de|Süd- und Nord-Dynastien|ja|南北朝|lt=Southern Dynasty|lt_ja=南朝|lt_de=Süd-Dynastie|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Southern and Northern Dynasties|qq=}}, during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Wu of Song|de|Kaiser Wu von Song|ja|宋武帝|zh|宋武帝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Wu of Song|qq=}}, it was decreed “Ban improper worship; eliminate all local temples.”

